<dl id="n03109a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03109a">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03109a"> 109(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ gentleman (Guido / Cavalcanti)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;&hellip;As I said, you&apos;re a <mark>gentleman</mark>. They say it takes three generations to make one. &hellip;&rdquo; <small> O. Henry, <a name="OHFM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#OHFM"><cite title="source">The Four Million</cite></a> (1906) [&lsquo;Mammon and the Archer&rsquo;] 128</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Guido Cavalcanti, Italian poet, was a friend of Dante. He was translated by Ezra Pound. </mm> </dd></dl>
